cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving the performance of DSRC communications in urban operations scenarios, which involves networking and communication protocols. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper discusses the issue of interference from civilian users and proposes a protocol to prioritize military users, which involves security and privacy concerns. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of DSRC in military applications, which may involve coordination and communication among multiple agents. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a protocol to prioritize military users, which may involve decision-making and optimization algorithms. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper discusses the challenge of congestion in DSRC and proposes a protocol to improve the performance of the system.
